20DeWitt%20did%20her%20best%20to%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmothers-childcare-working-parents-moms-good-bad-news-why-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espace%20for%20her%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%20alongside%20her%20new%20role%20as%20a%20parent.%20Working%20part%20time%20seemed%20like%20the%20best%20of%20both%20worlds%3B%20she%20could%20still%20get%20the%20satisfaction%20that%20came%20from%20her%20job%2C%20and%20the%20scaled-back%20hours%20would%20allow%20her%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20her%20son%20and%20cut%20down%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-parents-afford-childcare-get-stable-jobs-gbi-ubi-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20then%20DeWitt%20realized%20that%20reducing%20her%20schedule%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebelow%20full%20time%20would%20disqualify%20her%20family%20from%20healthcare%20coverage%20and%20make%20her%20ineligible%20for%20an%20employer-matched%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-great-recession-retirement-investment-lessons-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20husband%20was%20self-employed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20hold%20down%20the%20fort%20as%20far%20as%20our%20health%20insurance%20benefits%20went.%26quot%3B%20He%20recently%20switched%20to%20a%20corporate%20job%20so%20the%20family%20could%20have%20stable%20coverage%2C%20and%20DeWitt%20could%20continue%20splitting%20her%20schedule%20between%20the%20hospital%20and%20their%20baby%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20really%20important%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeWitt's%20dilemma%20is%20shared%20by%20parents%20and%20caregivers%20across%20America.%20Unlike%20other%20developed%20countries%2C%20the%20US%20offers%20few%20legal%20protections%20for%20part-time%20employees%2C%20meaning%20that%20people%20who%20typically%20work%20fewer%20than%2030%20to%2034%20hours%20a%20week%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eare%20left%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20their%20company's%20policies.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parenting-paradox-cant-afford-kids-waiting-older-career-pressure-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20are%20starting%20families%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20shift%20to%20working%20part%20time%20could%20be%20a%20perfect%20solution%20for%20new%20parents%20to%20stay%20connected%20to%20their%20careers%20while%20attending%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20their%20children.%20While%20some%20companies%20like%20Starbucks%20and%20UPS%20offer%20benefits%20to%20part-time%20workers%2C%20for%20most%20people%2C%20stepping%20back%20from%20full-time%20work%20can%20mean%20losing%20out%20on%20healthcare%20coverage%2C%20paid%20leave%2C%20and%20fair%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20the%20same%20position%2C%20the%20same%20qualifications%2C%20but%20you%20have%20one%20worker%20working%20full%20time%20and%20one%20worker%20working%20part%20time%2C%20and%20they%20are%20given%20different%20access%20to%20benefits%2C%20eligibility%20for%20promotions%2C%20or%20even%20paid%20differently%20based%20on%20hourly%20wages%2C%26quot%3B%20Laura%20Narefsky%2C%20a%20senior%20attorney%20at%20the%20National%20Women's%20Law%20Center%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-worried-unemployment-layoffs-recession-jobs-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%20is%20cooling%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20businesses%20are%20keen%20to%20keep%20valuable%20employees%20around%2C%20conversations%20with%20economists%2C%20policy%20analysts%2C%20company%20leaders%2C%20parents%2C%20and%20caregivers%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20expanding%20workers'%20ability%20to%20adjust%20their%20hours%20is%20a%20winning%20idea.%20Companies%20that%20allow%20parents%20to%20work%20part%20time%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretain%20experienced%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20save%20money%20on%20hiring.%20And%20letting%20more%20parents%2C%20especially%20mothers%2C%20stay%20connected%20to%20the%20workforce%20could%20be%20a%20path%20to%20economic%20growth%20as%20a%20whole%3A%20Nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Ffamee.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20part-time%20workers%20are%20parents%20with%20children%20under%206%20years%20old.%20America%20has%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20in%20terms%20of%20making%20the%20labor%20force%20flexible%20%E2%80%94%20but%20improving%20part-time%20opportunities%20is%20not%20only%20possible%2C%20it%20has%20overwhelmingly%20positive%20implications%20for%20the%20US%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fempsit.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E29%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20in%20the%20US%20work%20part%20time%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%2018%25%20of%20the%20total%20American%20labor%20force.%20Employees%20might%20choose%20a%20part-time%20schedule%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%3A%20They%20could%20be%20parents%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-xers-burdened-long-term-care-costs-for-boomers-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaregivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20need%20to%20be%20home%20to%20look%20after%20a%20loved%20one%3B%20some%20are%20students%20trying%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20while%20they%20finish%20a%20degree%3B%20others%20are%20retirees%2C%20people%20with%20disabilities%2C%20or%20people%20working%20multiple%20jobs.%20What%20all%20of%20these%20part-time%20workers%20have%20in%20common%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20federal%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFull-time%20employees%20in%20the%20US%20are%20guaranteed%20some%20basic%20rights%2C%20such%20as%20paid%20leave%20and%20access%20to%20company%20benefits.%20But%20once%20you%20dip%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebelow%20that%20roughly%2030-hour-a-week%20threshold%2C%20employees%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20safeguards.%20Workers%20told%20me%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20unpredictable%20schedules%20and%20tight%20budgets.%20Part-time%20workers%20are%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnwlc.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2FPart-time-workers-factsheet-v2-2.1.22.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20likely%20as%20full-time%20workers%20to%20hold%20a%20low-paying%20job%2C%20and%20many%20live%20near%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line.%20In%20a%202020%20report%2C%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%20found%20that%20part-time%20workers%20are%20paid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fpublication%2Fpart-time-pay-penalty%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%2020%25%20less%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20hour%20than%20their%20full-time%20counterparts%20in%20the%20same%20industry%20and%20occupation.%20And%20that%20doesn't%20include%20the%20money%20part-time%20workers%20lose%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20access%20to%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJulie%20Gagne%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E63%2C%20cobbles%20together%20part-time%20and%20gig%20work%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20while%20caring%20for%20her%20ex-husband%2C%20who%20is%20quadriplegic.%20She%20is%20a%20delivery%20driver%20near%20her%20home%20in%20Ann%20Arbor%2C%20Michigan%2C%20and%20often%20earns%20less%20than%20%2420%20an%20hour.%20It's%20enough%20to%20cover%20basic%20essentials%2C%20but%20she%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20build%20any%20savings%20and%20the%20job%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bphysically%20exhausting%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCandidly%2C%20I%20have%20not%20had%20health%20insurance%20in%20a%20very%2C%20very%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20healthy%2C%20but%20obviously%20if%20something%20catastrophic%20happened%2C%20I'd%20be%20screwed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F9Gojc%2F4%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Employee%20access%20to%20company%20benefits%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22478%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20level%20of%20economic%20uncertainty%20is%20particularly%20acute%20for%20parents.%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-childcare-costs-in-us-women-workforce-cheapest-countries-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20skyrocketed%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20outpacing%20salaries%20in%20some%20cities%2C%20many%20have%20been%20left%20in%20a%20bind.%20The%20lack%20of%20options%20hits%20moms%20especially%20hard.%20Deborah%20Singer%2C%20the%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20at%20the%20advocacy%20and%20research%20organization%20Moms%20First%2C%20said%20that%20mothers%20and%20female%20caregivers%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20drop%20to%20part-time%20hours%20or%20leave%20the%20workforce%20altogether.%20About%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fempsit.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix%20in%2010%3C%2Fa%3E%20part-time%20employees%20are%20women%2C%20and%20working%20fewer%20hours%20can%20have%20long-term%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20just%20a%20penalty%20that%20women%20are%20going%20to%20pay%20when%20their%20child%20is%20young%2C%26quot%3B%20Singer%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20impact%20their%20entire%20career%2C%20their%20retirement%20savings%2C%20and%20our%20economy%20more%20broadly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20access%20to%20a%20flexible%20schedule%20%E2%80%94%20without%20having%20to%20make%20major%20financial%20sacrifices%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20a%20game%20changer%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-kids-birth-rates-rising-costs-student-loan-debt-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennial%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20more%20of%20them%20to%20stay%20on%20the%20career%20ladder%20when%20their%20kids%20are%20toddlers%20or%20in%20preschool.%20Right%20now%2C%20though%2C%20many%20have%20to%20choose%20between%20a%20steady%20paycheck%20and%20time%20with%20their%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20Cuevas%2C%2035%2C%20lives%20in%20Chicago%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20their%20preschool-aged%20son%2C%20and%20toddler.%20After%20her%20first%20child%20was%20born%2C%20Cuevas%20knew%20she%20wanted%20to%20hang%20on%20to%20the%20successful%20career%20she'd%20built%20in%20academia.%20To%20save%20on%20childcare%20bills%2C%20she%20switched%20from%20a%20full-time%20role%20in%20college%20admissions%20and%20education%20policy%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20a%20part-time%20job%20as%20a%20college%20counselor%20for%20a%20nonprofit.%20The%20move%20helped%20her%20stay%20in%20the%20field%20she's%20passionate%20about%2C%20but%20she%20said%20she%20lost%20her%20access%20to%20employer%20healthcare%20and%20retirement%20plans.%20Her%20pay%20is%20unpredictable%20month-to-month%2C%20and%20she%20hopes%20to%20return%20to%20full-time%20work%20as%20soon%20as%20her%20youngest%20son%20goes%20to%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20became%20a%20mom%2C%20and%20as%20much%20as%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20there%20for%20my%20family%2C%20I%20also%20didn't%20want%20to%20lose%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20frustrated%20with%20companies%20and%20employers%20for%20putting%20the%20load%20directly%20on%20mom%3A%20What%20if%20she%20also%20wants%20to%20grow%3F%20What%20if%20she%20also%20wants%20to%20scale%20up%3F%20What%20if%20she%20also%20wants%20to%20get%20paid%20more%20than%20her%20partner%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20protections%20for%20part-time%20workers%20makes%20the%20US%20an%20anomaly%20compared%20to%20many%20of%20its%20peer%20countries%20such%20as%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Sweden%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20Spain.%20In%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20for%20example%2C%20part-time%20workers%20are%20required%20by%20law%20to%20have%20the%20same%20access%20to%20benefits%2C%20time%20off%2C%20and%20pensions%20as%20full-time%20employees.%20Not%20extending%20these%20rights%20to%20part-time%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20isn't%20just%20a%20burden%20on%20the%20individuals%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20holding%20back%20the%20nation's%20economy%20as%20a%20whole.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKathryn%20Anne%20Edwards%2C%20an%20economist%20who%20studies%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20economic%20inequality%2C%20said%20providing%20more%20rights%20for%20part-time%20employees%20could%20boost%20the%20American%20labor%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20labor%20market%20is%20much%20meaner%20and%20exclusive%20than%20people%20realize%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BOur%20labor%20market%20is%20very%20much%20like%2C%20'If%20you%20can't%20hack%20it%2C%20you're%20out'%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20people's%20participation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20Netherlands%3A%20As%20of%202023%2C%20the%20country's%20labor-force%20participation%20rate%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feures.europa.eu%2Fliving-and-working%2Flabour-market-information%2Flabour-market-information-netherlands_en%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E73%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20a%20slightly%20higher%20rate%20for%20men%20(76%25)%20than%20women%20(68%25)%2C%20largely%20thanks%20to%20the%20prevalence%20of%20part-time%20work.%20At%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20the%20US%20labor-force%20participation%20rate%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fopub%2Fmlr%2F2024%2Farticle%2Funemployment-rate-inches-up-during-2023-labor-force-participation-rises.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E62.5%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20sharper%20gap%20between%20men%20(68.2%25)%20and%20women%20(57.3%25).%20Historically%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-industries-are-hiring-employment-cant-find-job-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20people%20are%20working%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20positive%20downstream%20effects%20like%20higher%20consumer%20spending%20and%20more%20movement%20in%20the%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20US%20labor%20market%20needs%20is%20a%20'glow-up%2C'%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20said.%20But%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20laws%20protecting%20part-time%20employees%20will%20be%20passed%20at%20the%20federal%20level%20anytime%20soon.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F117th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F3641%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPart-Time%20Worker%20Bill%20of%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20ensure%20that%20all%20part-time%20employees%20have%20access%20to%20paid%20leave%20and%20other%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20House%20in%202023%2C%20but%20the%20bill%20has%20gone%20nowhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20companies%20can%20take%20steps%20to%20protect%20part-time%20workers%2C%20even%20without%20government%20involvement.%20UPS%20offers%20pensions%20and%20some%20healthcare%20coverage%20for%20part-time%20employees%2C%20and%20Trader%20Joe's%20offers%20medical%2C%20dental%2C%20and%20vision%20benefits%2C%20along%20with%20access%20to%20a%20401(k)%20for%20most%20part-time%20employees.%20The%20moves%20aren't%20just%20a%20moral%20imperative%20for%20these%20companies%2C%20they%20also%20have%20material%20benefits%20for%20their%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20March%20report%20for%20BI%20using%20data%20from%20400%2C000-plus%20small%20and%20midsize%20businesses%2C%20the%20business%20research%20firm%20Gusto%20found%20that%20the%20average%20job%20tenure%20for%20part-time%20workers%20with%20healthcare%20benefits%20is%2039%20months%2C%20compared%20to%2036%20months%20for%20full-time%20workers%20and%2023%20months%20for%20part-time%20workers%20without%20healthcare%20benefits.%20Employees%20who%20had%20access%20to%20paid%20vacation%20time%20and%20retirement%20plans%20were%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20stay%20at%20their%20companies%20than%20those%20who%20didn't.%20When%20experienced%20talent%20stays%20at%20a%20company%2C%20employers%20don't%20have%20to%20spend%20money%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-labor-market-hiring-layoffs-quits-recession-sahm-rule-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efill%20open%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FAiL9a%2F4%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20job%20tenure%20based%20on%20benefits%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22255%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-brian-niccol-changes-6-months-in-pulse-check-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStarbucks%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20implemented%20similar%20part-time%20work%20benefits.%20It%20offers%20full%20tuition%20for%20full-%20and%20part-time%20employees%20pursuing%20a%20degree%2C%20parental%20leave%20for%20part-time%20employees%20working%20at%20least%2020%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20401(k)%20matches%2C%20and%20healthcare%20coverage.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Starbucks%20told%20me%20that%20most%20of%20the%20company's%20barista%20employees%20are%20part%20time.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20employee%20retention%20at%20the%20chain%20is%20at%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20company%20believes%20its%20benefit%20policies%20play%20a%20big%20role%20in%20that.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20has%20seen%20a%20boost%20in%20traffic%20to%20its%20Careers%20webpage%20since%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-changes-paid-parental-leave-policy-baristas-18-weeks-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenhanced%20parental%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20policy%20for%20full-%20and%20part-time%20workers%20began%20on%20March%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJamie-Lee%20Kapana%2C%2033%2C%20is%20a%20barista%20in%20Oahu%20and%20has%20a%2013-year-old%20son.%20She's%20been%20working%20part%20time%20at%20Starbucks%20since%20he%20was%20a%20toddler.%20Kapana%20said%20that%20with%20past%20service-industry%20jobs%2C%20she%20struggled%20to%20find%20the%20flexibility%20she%20needed%20as%20a%20new%20mom%20while%20still%20paying%20the%20bills.%20Starbucks'%20health%2C%20401(k)%2C%20and%20other%20benefits%20have%20been%20a%20game%20changer%20for%20her%20family%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20decided%20to%20leave%20the%20restaurant%20job%20and%20commit%20to%20Starbucks%20because%20of%20the%20health%20benefits%2C%20job%20flexibility%2C%20and%20consistent%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20Kapana%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20advantages%20was%20being%20able%20to%20work%20just%2020%20hours%20a%20week%20to%20receive%20these%20benefits%2C%20not%20just%20for%20myself%2C%20but%20also%20for%20my%20son.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20white-collar%20industries%20are%20leaning%20into%20part-time%20work%20as%20well.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hiringlab.org%2F2024%2F06%2F20%2Fpart-time-opportunities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20hiring%20platform%20Indeed%20found%20that%20part-time%20job%20postings%20in%20sectors%20like%20beauty%20and%20wellness%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20communications%20rose%20by%20up%20to%2027%25%20between%202022%20and%202024.%20Still%2C%20higher-paying%20sectors%20like%20insurance%2C%20law%2C%20and%20finance%20remain%20heavily%20tilted%20toward%20full-time%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20accessible%20workforce%20is%20a%20win-win%20for%20employees%20and%20employers.%20Companies%20can%20retain%20talent%2C%20and%20parents%20can%20achieve%20a%20healthy%20work-life%20balance.%20Plus%2C%20as%20Edwards%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bmore%20workers%20equals%20a%20bigger%20economy%2C%20full%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fallie-kelly%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAllie%20Kelly%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Economy%20team.%20She%20writes%20about%20social%20safety%20nets%20and%20how%20policy%20impacts%20people.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parents-kids-childcare-careers-part-time-jobs-america-salary-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745050622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ed4727b8b41a9673fc665d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parents-kids-childcare-careers-part-time-jobs-america-salary-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22America's%20parents%20are%20balancing%20babies%20and%20career%20growth.%20One%20simple%20policy%20could%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20them%20to%20do%20both.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parents-kids-childcare-careers-part-time-jobs-america-salary-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tesla%20owner%20files%20class-action%20suit%20over%20warranty-voiding%20odometers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745050612000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22ht