bout%20Path%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20in%202012%20to%20top%20executives%20in%20a%20thread%20named%20%26quot%3BAquarium%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20tongue-in-cheek%20name%20for%20one%20of%20the%20social%20network's%20real-life%20conference%20rooms%20at%20its%20Menlo%20Park%20HQ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOut%20of%20all%20the%20new%20social%20startups%2C%20they're%20the%20only%20one%20that%20goes%20right%20to%20the%20core%20of%20what%20we're%20trying%20to%20do%20around%20identity%20and%20friend%20sharing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221356%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%202012%20email%20sent%20by%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680290eac6ad288d147e964a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EProsecutors%20showed%20a%202012%20email%20sent%20by%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20about%20his%20worries%20surrounding%20Path%2C%20a%20then-growing%20social%20networking%20app.%3Cp%3EFTC%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg's%20old%20worries%20are%20more%20relevant%20when%20they%20concern%20Instagram%20and%20WhatsApp.%20The%20FTC%20contends%20that%20Facebook%20gobbled%20up%20the%20companies%20because%20it%20worried%20that%2C%20with%20a%20large%20user%20base%2C%20either%20one%20could%20eventually%20pivot%20to%20become%20more%20like%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Instagram%20continues%20to%20kick%20ass%20on%20mobile%20or%20if%20Google%20buys%20them%2C%20then%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%20they%20could%20easily%20add%20pieces%20of%20their%20service%20that%20copy%20what%20we're%20doing%20now%2C%20and%20if%20they%20have%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20people's%20photos%20then%20that's%20a%20real%20issue%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20in%20a%202011%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229015bfde-4519-4b39-9279-dc03676a8384%5C%22%3ESometimes%20it's%20not%20about%20being%20Liked.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20WhatsApp%2C%20the%20government%20showed%20multiple%20messages%20where%20Zuckerberg%20expressed%20concern%20about%20the%20messaging%20app%20that%20rose%20to%20popularity%20outside%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20where%20he%20seemed%20unmoved%20by%20its%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20found%20him%20fairly%20impressive%20although%20disappointingly%20(or%20maybe%20positive%20for%20us)%20unambitious%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20in%202012%20to%20colleagues%20after%20he%20met%20Jan%20Koum%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20WhatsApp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Meta%20CEO%20seemed%20taken%20aback%20when%20Hansen%20asked%20Zuckerberg%20about%20the%20email.%20Zuckerberg%20said%20the%20point%20of%20his%20message%20was%20that%20he%20had%20learned%20Koum%20did%20not%20want%20to%20pivot%20or%20monetize%20WhatsApp%20in%20a%20way%20that%20would%20truly%20unnerve%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20the%20FTC%20showed%20multiple%20messages%20in%20which%20Zuckerberg%20expressed%20frustration%20with%20Facebook's%20efforts%20to%20develop%20a%20competing%20camera%20app%20as%20Instagram%20skyrocketed%20in%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20going%20in%20with%20our%20photos%20team%3F%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%20in%20a%202011%20message%20that%20was%20partially%20redacted%20when%20it%20was%20presented%20in%20court.%20%26quot%3BBetween%20%5Bredacted%5D%20leaving%20and%20%5Bredacted%5D%20being%20checked%20out%2Fa%20bad%20manager%20as%20well%20as%20%5Bredacted%5D%20also%20being%20checked%20out%20and%20%5Bredacted%5D%20not%20wanting%20to%20work%20with%20this%20team%20because%20he%20thinks%20this%20team%20sucks.%20It%20seems%20like%20we%20have%20a%20really%20critical%20situation%20to%20fix%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzuckerberg-meta-antitrust-trial-emails-ftc-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745050261000